Defines `SummError`, the single error enum returned by every fallible operation in the ctx-summarize runner (path resolution, prompt loading, agent invocation, access control, scope gating, filesystem I/O), built with `thiserror` for `Display`/`Error` impls.

Notable variants: `AccessDenied { path, reason }` — the deny-by-default gate that blocks secret/binary/ignored files even if explicitly named as a target; `ScopeTooLarge { count, max }` — the target-count gate requiring `--approve` to bypass; `NoAgentCommand` — signals the agent command must come from `CTX_AGENT_CMD` env var or a target's `.env` file, with no other fallback. `Io` and other variants store stringified paths/details rather than wrapping source errors, so no `#[from]` conversions exist — callers must construct variants explicitly with already-formatted strings.

No behavior lives here; it's a pure data/display definition. Any caller matching on these variants (e.g. CLI exit-code mapping) will break if variant names or field shapes change.